In addition to above comments - there is the same layout used for every provider. In cases like this why not just extract them to a reusable component so we can make changes in one spot (like the icon) and have it go to all places.

They even all share the same text prefix, so its much easier
```js
// rest of code
{LLMSelection.policyUrl && <PolicyLink url={LLMSelection.policyUrl} />}
//

//jsx component
function PolicyLink({ url }) {
  return (
    <div className="text-theme-text-secondary text-sm">
    Your usage, chats, and data are subject to the service&apos;s{" "}
    <Link
      className="text-theme-text-secondary hover:text-theme-text-primary text-sm font-medium underline transition-colors inline-flex items-center gap-1"
      to={url}
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
    >
      privacy policy
      <ArrowSquareOut weight="fill" size={18} className="text-theme-text-secondary" />
    </Link>
  </div>
  );
}
```

Can do the same for the description listing as well.

